  <main class="container" style="padding-top:2rem;padding-bottom:2rem;">
    <section class="content">
      <h2 id="abstract">Abstract</h2>
      <p>ZION is a consciousness-based blockchain designed to align material value with humanitarian impact and spiritual development. The TestNet explores a mining model with multipliers, long-horizon governance transition, and a transparent allocation for social good.</p>

      <h2 id="tokenomics">Tokenomics (TestNet model)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Total Supply</strong>: 144,000,000,000 ZION (long-term issuance ~50 years).</li>
        <li><strong>Block Time</strong>: ~2 minutes (target).</li>
        <li><strong>Block Reward</strong>: ~5,479.45 ZION (subject to distribution rules).</li>
        <li><strong>Allocation (illustrative)</strong>:
          <ul>
            <li>~87.67% Miners (with consciousness multipliers applied)</li>
            <li>~10% Humanitarian Fund</li>
            <li>~1% Development</li>
            <li>~1.33% Other initiatives</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">Values are indicative for TestNet documentation and may evolve. Refer to release notes for finalized parameters per phase.</div>

      <h2 id="consensus">Consensus & Mining</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Multi-Algorithm Mining</strong>: RandomX (CPU-friendly), Autolykos v2 (GPU-friendly), and an experimental “Cosmic Harmony” track (TestNet research focus).</li>
        <li><strong>ASIC-Resistance Goals</strong>: Encourage decentralization and broad participation.</li>
        <li><strong>Security</strong>: Standard cryptographic assumptions with community-driven audits and iterative hardening.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="consciousness">Consciousness Mining (Concept)</h2>
      <p>Participants receive reward multipliers based on development levels. The TestNet evaluates options for fair and ethical mechanisms.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Levels (1→9): Physical → Emotional → Intellectual → Intuitive → Mental → Spiritual → Cosmic → Galactic → On The Star</li>
        <li>Multipliers: 1× to 15× (indicative)</li>
        <li>Intent: Align incentives with community ethics and humanitarian outcomes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="governance">Governance & Treasury</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>20-year transition</strong> toward full DAO governance.</li>
        <li><strong>Treasury transparency</strong> with public reporting and community oversight.</li>
        <li><strong>Proposal process</strong> to prioritize projects (education, healthcare, welfare).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="parameters">Key Parameters (current TestNet view)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Block time: 2 minutes</li>
        <li>Block reward: ~5,479.45 ZION</li>
        <li>Total supply: 144B ZION (long horizon)</li>
        <li>Golden Egg Quest (HIRANYAGARBHA): special challenge with significant rewards (TestNet narrative)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="roadmap">Roadmap & Risks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Iterative TestNet phases with stability and security milestones</li>
        <li>Open research on consciousness multipliers and measurement approaches</li>
        <li>Governance frameworks: community feedback and pilots</li>
        <li>Risks: mechanism manipulation, governance capture, regulatory changes</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="note">This Lite version is a high-level orientation for TestNet. A full whitepaper will include formal specifications and proofs as components stabilize.</div>
    </section>
